Title: A Survey Of Oscillations And Granulation In Subgiant Stars

PI: Buzasi, Derek - Florida Gulf Coast University

Summary: TESS has proven to be a highly effective tool for the detection and characterization of stellar oscillations across the HR diagram, and for the understanding of stellar granulation among stars with outer convective envelopes. However, the current census of subgiant stars with detected oscillations and granulation is focused on the Kepler field, and TESS long-cadence observations in many cases do not provide sufficiently long time series to enable resolution of complex frequency patterns. We request 2-minute cadence observations to perform a survey of oscillations and granulation in a large sample of subgiant stars, which will enable investigations into the convective driving and damping of oscillations, the calibration of granulation metrics, and insights into the physics of convection.
